/*Below line of code is written in Build Steps of freestyle project
1. Copied the docker-compose file of 2tierapplication into jenkins workspace path - /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/twotierhtmlapp
2. added jenkins user to docker group
3. first changing the directory to twotierhtmlapp folder so jenkins can access docker-compose file.
4. then brought the docker compose file up, halted/ made the pipeline wait for 60 secs to check containers are up and running
5. user cleanup() to kill and remove the container by using docker compose down
6. user trap command to execute the cleanup() at the end of all the actions in the file.
*/
cleanup() {
docker compose down -v
}

trap cleanup EXIT 

cd /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/twotierhtmlapp
docker compose up -d
sleep 60
